node.title: Tasmania records 1,037 new COVID-19 cases
node.alt: Rapid antigen test with negative result.
node.description: Tasmania has recorded a rise in new COVID-19 cases to 1,037, up from 825 yesterday.Â
node.content: ["Tasmania has recorded 1,037 new COVID-19 cases in the last 24 hours, up from 825 yesterday.\u00a0", "Twenty-one people are in hospital and one person remains in intensive care.\u00a0", "There are 6,365\u00a0actives cases in the state,\u00a0 down slightly from yesterday's figure of 6,485.\u00a0", "There were 310 PCR tests conducted and 727 rapid antigen tests.\u00a0", "Just over 5,800 rapid tests were distributed yesterday.\u00a0", "More to come."]
